Node.Notes: (SYNTAX) Either O with some action like "he finds" understood or P "there is nothing."
Perhaps something like "Many people proclaim, each, his unfailling love."
Apparently refers to dishonest practice of using different sets of weights/measures for buying and selling so as to cheat others.
Poor quality or bad bargain, said with intention to drive down the price.
Strange woman (see also pr27:13), either simply in sense of stranger or seductress/wayward woman.
Most prefer the Ketiv (a verbal form) over the nominal Qere. Sense seems to be that physical punishment is good for cleansing/getting rid of moral evil.
